<h2>Atom Package InstallScripts</h2>

<p>On macOS and Linux systems, during the installation of this atom package, Reactor will ask for your permission to launch an "<a href="https://gitlab.com/WeSuckLess/Reactor/blob/master/Docs/Creating-Atom-Packages.md#installscripts-and-uninstallscripts">InstallScript</a>" code snippet that runs the "chmod -R 755" shell command on each of the "Bin" Category based atom package's executable CLI (command-line) programs. This is required so the CLI programs can be started by the Lua based KartaVR menu items. If you would like the KartaVR lua scripts to be able to perform correctly, you have to approve each of the InstallScript dialog requests manually (which is displayed in a syntax highlighted Lua code snippet preview window).</p>

<p>Note: You have the option to approve or skip running each of the InstallScript code blocks, if you wish, and then can manually adjust the Reactor Bin folder content's disk permissions manually on your own.</p>


